article_title: 2 Council Bluffs police officers receive minor injuries while arresting teen boy, his grandma

og.description: The incident occurred after police were called to the Family Dollar store at 2801 West Broadway about 3:30 p.m. and learned that a 57-year-old Council Bluffs woman became upset because the store wouldn’t accept a coupon for a purchase, according to Sgt. Brandon Danielson. Officers began to place the woman under arrest on suspicion of causing a disturbance.
